Region Synthetic Controls

We want to create synthetic controls at the region-level.

The outcome variable is

  • number of purchases made in a region each week.

The matching covariates are:

  • number of users
  • number of restaurants
  • average number of purchases made by users per week?
  • average amount spent by users
  • average number of sales made by restaurant per day
  • average amount spent at restaurants
  • average rating of restaurants

In the code below I count the total number of transactions per region per week. This is the outcome variable.

df_purchases <- df_cust_trans_exist %>% 
  filter(week >= 7 & week != 11 & week <= 15) %>% 
  group_by(rest_area_id, week, treated) %>% 
  summarise(purchases = n())

In the code below I use data from the customer - weekly level to calculate trials per region per week.

df_cust_area <- df_cust_trans_exist %>% 
  group_by(cust_id) %>% 
  summarise(cust_area_id = mfv(rest_area_id))
df_trials <- df_cust_longer_NA %>% 
  select(cust_id, week, distinct) %>% 
  filter(week >= 7 & week != 11 & week <= 15) %>% 
  left_join(df_cust_area, by = c("cust_id")) %>% 
  group_by(cust_area_id, week) %>% 
  summarise(trials = sum(distinct, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
  rename(rest_area_id = cust_area_id)

In the code below I count the distinct number of customers per region, and distinct number of restaurants per region. The problem with the number of customers is that it will double count customers who have purchased from restaurants in different regions.

df_num <- df_cust_trans_exist %>% 
  filter(week >= 7 & week < 11) %>% 
  group_by(rest_area_id) %>% 
  summarise(num_cust = n_distinct(cust_id),
            num_rest = n_distinct(rest_id))

In the code below I find the average frequency of purchase by users per region in the pre experiment period.

df_cust <- df_cust_longer_NA %>% 
  filter(week >= 7 & week < 11) %>% 
  left_join(df_cust_area, by = c("cust_id")) %>% 
  group_by(cust_area_id) %>%
  summarise(avg_cust_spend = mean(avg_spend),
            avg_freq_week = mean(count)) %>%
  rename(rest_area_id = cust_area_id)

In the code below I create restaurant characteristics at the region level.

df_rest <- df_cust_trans_exist %>% 
  group_by(rest_area_id) %>% 
  summarise(avg_sales = mean(rest_daily_sales),
            avg_bill = mean(rest_pre_bill),
            avg_rating = mean(rest_pre_rating))

In the code below I join the data frames and add some filters to make the data compatible with the synth package.

df_synth <- df_purchases %>% 
  filter(rest_area_id != 302 & rest_area_id != 303) %>% 
  left_join(df_trials, by = c("rest_area_id", "week")) %>% 
  left_join(df_num, by = c("rest_area_id")) %>% 
  left_join(df_cust, by = c("rest_area_id")) %>% 
  left_join(df_rest, by = c("rest_area_id")) %>% 
  as.data.frame()

Both outcomes, all covariates

cov.var <- c("num_cust", "num_rest", "avg_freq_week", "avg_cust_spend", "avg_sales", "avg_bill", "avg_rating")
match.out <- c("purchases", "trials")

synth <- microsynth(df_synth,
                    idvar = "rest_area_id", timevar = "week", intvar = "treated",
                    start.pre = 7, end.pre = 10, end.post = 15,
                    match.out = match.out, match.covar = cov.var,
                    result.var = match.out, omnibus.var = match.out,
                    use.backup = TRUE,
                    n.cores = min(parallel::detectCores(), 2))
